programme.title: It Follows
programme.desc: In this relentless and innovative horror film, a 19-year-old woman contracts a sexually transmitted curse after a one-night stand with a handsome stranger. Terrorized by malevolent phantoms, she turns to her friends to find a way out of this nightmare.

programme.title: Grizzly II: Revenge
programme.desc: All hell breaks loose when a giant grizzly, reacting to the slaughter of her cubs by poachers, attacks a massive rock concert in the National Park. [This sequel to "Grizzly" (1976) was left unfinished after production wrapped prematurely in 1983, and was not officially released until 2020, though a bootleg workprint version had been in circulation for some years prior to this.]

programme.title: Agent Revelation
programme.desc: A mysteriously contolling ancient dust has its way overcoming humans, but somehow it gives Jim Yung superpowers. As a result, he is taken to a training ground where he must learn why aliens have returned to Earth.

programme.title: The Match
programme.desc: It is the spring of 1944 and the Nazis are preparing to commemorate the birthday of their beloved leader, Adolf Hitler. One activity they come up with is a football match between an elite Nazi team and a ragtag team of prisoners. With the help of a former captain of the national football team, the determined team made up of ex-footballers and prisoners of war will do all they can to defeat their captors in a game where all odds are stacked against them.

programme.title: McEnroe
programme.desc: The story of a legend told by the legend himself: John McEnroe. Nobody embodied the rockstar era of tennis more than John McEnroe. The original bad boy of the sport, McEnroe was famous not only for his epic matches, but also for his confrontations on and off the court. Accompanied by interviews with icons like Patty Smyth, Keith Richards, Billie Jean King, and Bjorn Borg, the legendary tennis ace gives an unflinching account of his triumphs, struggles, friendships, and rivalries.

programme.title: Another Kind of Wedding
programme.desc: Matthew and Louisa's marriage day falls apart when their dysfunctional family tries to fix their broken relationships. The beautiful ceremony spirals into a chaotic circus when ex-lovers, separated parents, insults, and even punches get mixed into the situation.

programme.title: American Hangman
programme.desc: An unidentified man posts a live feed that shows his kidnapped victims and says he plans to kill one before the day ends. It eventually becomes clear that the people online are the ones who will act as the judge for this "trial."

programme.title: Unfaithful
programme.desc: "Fatal Attraction" director Adrian Lyne tackles infidelity once again with this involving erotic thriller. Oscar nominee Diane Lane and Richard Gere are superb as a happily married couple whose union is threatened when the wife begins an affair with an attractive book dealer (Olivier Martinez). Erik Per Sullivan, Myra Lucretia Taylor.

programme.title: Game 6
programme.desc: Disappointing tale set during the 1986 World Series follows a playwright and Boston Red Sox fan (Michael Keaton) as he sweats out the opening of his new play. Robert Downey Jr., Catherine O'Hara, Griffin Dunne. Directed by Michael Hoffman from a script by popular novelist Don DeLillo (his first screenplay).

programme.title: Friedkin Uncut
programme.desc: Eighty-three-year-old William Friedkin, director of films including "The French Connection" and "The Exorcist," is joined by colleagues and admirers in reminiscing about his life and storied career.

When strange creatures begin attacking people in the subway system, she joins forces with the police to eradicate what turns out to be a breed of giant man-eating insects. Jeremy Northam, Josh Brolin, Giancarlo Giannini, Charles S. Dutton. Directed by Guillermo Del Toro.

programme.title: Mimic 2
programme.desc: Mutated bugs still plague the sewers of New York City in this unsettling sequel to the 1997 horror film. This time out, a cop (Bruno Campos) investigates a series of hideous murders that he traces to an entomologist who's being stalked by killer bugs. Alix Koromzay, Will Estes, Joseph Hodge, Jon Polito, Bob Rumnock. Directed by Jean de Segonzac.

programme.title: Mimic: Sentinel
programme.desc: Evil bugs run amok in this stylish third entry in the "Mimic" horror-film franchise. A sickly man (Karl Geary), who passes his time taking photos of the people outside his apartment, discovers that giant, mutated insects have invaded his neighborhood. With help from his sister (Alexis Dziena), he tries to end the mayhem. J.T. Petty directed. Lance Henriksen, Amanda Plummer.

programme.desc: Angered that God gave souls to humans, Gabriel (Christopher Walken) leads an army of evil angels to raise hell on Earth. Elias Koteas. Katherine: Virginia Madsen. Simon: Eric Stoltz. Rachel: Amanda Plummer. Gregory Widen directed.

programme.title: The Prophecy II
programme.desc: Christopher Walken reprises his role as evil archangel Gabriel in this thrilling sequel. As the war of the angels rages on, Gabriel is granted a release from hell in order to prevent Christ's Second Coming---but his real intention is to betray Satan and seize control of Heaven. Jennifer Beals, Russell Wong, Eric Roberts, Brittany Murphy, Glenn Danzig, Bruce Abbott, William Prael, Steve Hytner, Renee Victor, Elizabeth Dennehy.

programme.title: The Prophecy 3: The Ascent
programme.desc: Christopher Walken resumes his role as Gabriel, the fallen archangel, in this thrilling third installment of the chilling supernatural horror series about warring angels. This time, Gabriel is protector to a child born of an angel and a human. The child is the only one who can stop Pyriel, the evil angel of genocide, from destroying the world. Scott Cleverdon, Vincent Spano, Brad Dourif.
